===Phonosemantic interpretation===

[[w:Old_Chinese|Old Chinese]] [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Initials|Initial]] {{IPAchar|/*n-/}} lends semantic value '''Supple'''. [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Tones_and_final_consonants|Final consonant]] {{IPAchar|/*-m/}} lends semantic value '''Encompass'''.
[[w:Seal_script|Seal script style]] shows a combination of two elements: [[w:Radical_(Chinese_character)#Semantic_elements|semantic indicator]] [[屮]] grass shoot + [[冂]] boundary/enclosure + [[w:Chinese_character_classification#Phono-semantic_compound_characters|phono-semantic indicator]] an inverted [[入]] (enter) pierced by two horizontal lines → sprouts placed inside a hothouse for cultivation.
Source: [http://www.kanjinetworks.com/eng/kanji-dictionary/online-kanji-etymology-dictionary.cfm?kanji_id=NAM04 Howell & Morimoto]

===Etymology===
{{liushu|p}}: a hanging percussion instrument.

Borrowed for the word "south," for unknown reasons (phonetic resemblance?). Originally identical to the left side of [[殼]].

